<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Chairman Received by Indian House Speaker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Chairman Received by Indian House Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204150794 Hanoi VNA in English 1446 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2204150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 22 -- Speaker of the Indian House of 
Commons [as received] Shivraj Patil [speaker of the Indian Lok 
Sabha] received in New Delhi yesterday afternoon Vietnam's 
National Assembly Chairman Nong Duc Manh and his party now on an 
official visit to India. 
  Speaking during the reception, Chairman Nong Duc Manh said 
he 
treasured the close friendship and solidarity between Vietnam 
and India which had been fostered by President Ho Chi Minh and 
Prime Minister J. Nehru. He stressed that the renovation 
process and expansion of the cooperation ties with other 
countries over the world was a good opportunity for Vietnam to 
learn experience from foreign countries including India. He 
invited Mr Shivraj Patil to visit Vietnam, and expressed his 
wish for further cooperation between the two legislatures. 
  Mr. Patil accepted Mr. Manh's invitation with pleasure. The 
former spoke highly of the achievements recorded by the 
Vietnamese people, and he wished that the all-sided cooperation 
between Vietnam and India would continue to develop to a higher 
level. 
  Later the Vietnamese delegation met with 30 Indian 
parliamentarians of various parties from different states. 
  The same day speaker Shivraj Patil gave a banquet in honour 
of the Vietnamese National Assembly Chairman and his party. 

</TEXT>

