<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vo Van Kiet Speaks at Regional Economic Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vo Van Kiet Speaks at Regional Economic Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204154394 Hanoi VNA in English 1504 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2204154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 22 -- The third conference on sub- 
regional economic cooperation was opened here this morning in 
the Presence of P.M. Vo Van Kiet and Asian Development Bank 
[ADB] President Mitsuo Sato. 
  The conference are attended by high-level delegations of the 
Governments of Thailand, Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar [Burma] and the 
People's Republic of China and Vietnam. ADB senior officials 
and ambassadors and charge d'affaires of the participant 
countries are also on hand. 
  After the opening speech delivered by Deputy Prime Minister 
Tran Duc Luong, head of the Vietnamese delegation to the 
conference, Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet delivered a speech in 
which he said the high-level conference on sub-regional economic 
cooperation initiated by ADB was highly valued and actively 
responded by the countries concerned including Vietnam. 
  He said the Vietnamese Government pledged to extended 
support 
and cooperation in sub-regional projects, and called for 
financial assistance from the international community to carry 
out these projects. The Vietnamese leader expressed his hope 
that this conference would mark an important step in the process 
of cooperation in the sub-region and wished it a success. 
  Many papers on projects of cooperation in various fields 
including energy, transport, communications, tourism and trade 
were also delivered at the conference. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

