<F P=106> [From MAINICHI SHIMBUN 26 April Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Michio Watanabe, Liberal Democratic Party member and 
former deputy prime minister and foreign minister, commented on 
the new administration led by Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata on 25 
April. He said: "I would like (Hata) to carry out Shinseito's 
original policies. I will cooperate in implementing policies 
that are beneficial for Japan, and will not cooperate with those 
that are not." 

</TEXT>

