<H3> <TI>   Political Dialogue With Strikers Ineffective </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Dialogue With Strikers Ineffective </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2504140794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1300 GMT 25 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2504140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 25 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Continuing 
political consultations of the leaderships of the Mongolian 
National Democratic Party, Mongolian Social Democratic Party, 
Mongolian Democratic Association, Union of Mongolian Students 
and Union for New Progress with the participants of the hunger 
strike lasting for 15 days already who are demanding the 
resignation of the government have so far resulted in nothing. 
The disagreement existing between the participating sides is 
apparently telling on in reference to the issue of the further 
ways and perspectives for continuing the political struggle. 
  The press conference scheduled to be held today at the 
headquarters of the political strike has not been held and the 
reasons for its postponing to tomorrow have not been announced. 

</TEXT>

