<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hunger Strike Reportedly Called Off </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hunger Strike Reportedly Called Off </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2504140994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1307 GMT 25 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2504140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 25 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- It has 
been announced here that the hunger strike at the central square 
of the Ulaanbaatar city which lasts 292 hours and was called by 
the members and supporters of the Mongolian Democratic 
Association and the Union of Mongolian Students and the Union 
for New Progress having been demanding the resignation of the 
incumbent government of Mongolia has been stopped today. As is 
reported the leader of the Mongolian Democratic Association T. 
Elbegdorj declaring the decision on stopping the hunger strike 
said that here that "the present government is not worth dying 
for it." The events around the hunger strike has shown the 
actual face of the leadership of the government and the 
parliament. To stop the hunger strike, he noted in this 
respect, does not mean the completion of our struggle. It would 
be continuing and expanding up to an organization of a general 
strike and our demands are remaining in force. It is not the 
time yet to speak about who is the winner and who is the loser. 
We have attained a great success by that in accordance with our 
demands there has been laid down proper foundations for 
establishing free means of mass information media in Mongolian 
society. 

</TEXT>

