<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thai Ambassador Calls on Sihanouk 22 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Thai Ambassador Calls on Sihanouk 22 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2604095694 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the Foreign Ministry's Information 
Department, on 22 April Thai ambassador to Phnom Penh Sakthip 
Krairoek called on King Norodom Sihanouk and Queen Monique at 
their palace. The following is the essence of the meeting: 
  On behalf of the Thai Government and the Thai people, the 
ambassador expressed pleasure that the king's health has 
improved, which enabled him to return to Cambodia to the delight 
of the Cambodian people. The ambassador also congratulated and 
expressed support for the king's proposal to hold a round-table 
meeting of the leaders of Cambodian factions -- Samdech Norodom 
Ranariddh, Samdech Chea Sim, Samdech Hun Sen, and Khieu Samphan 
-- during 2-5 May. The Thai envoy expressed the view that due 
to the respect and acceptance of all Cambodians, King Sihanouk 
is currently the only person to be able to achieve national 
reconciliation. The Thai Government sincerely wishes to see 
national reconciliation materialized in Cambodia as well as 
peace and progress there like in other countries in the region. 
  On Thai-Cambodian relations, King Sihanouk felt that 
accusations and counteraccusations through the mass media should 
end. It would be better for the two countries to use diplomatic 
measures or government-level contacts. 
  The Thai envoy emphasized that the Thai Government 
recognizes 
the Cambodian Government as the sole legitimate administration 
of Cambodia and that it does not support the Khmer Rouge. The 
Thai Government is determined to maintain good relations and see 
the neighboring countries, including Cambodia, enjoy stability 
and prosperity. It reiterates continued support for the 
Cambodian government's national reconstruction efforts. 

</TEXT>

