<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sihanouk Tells Khieu Samphan of Roundtable Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sihanouk Tells Khieu Samphan of Roundtable Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2504130094 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1100 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2504130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1100 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Message of His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, king of </F>
Cambodia, to His Excellency Khieu Samphan, chairman of the Party 
of Democratic Kampuchea"; dated 24 April -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] After receiving your important and detailed letter 
concerning especially the issues of your security and a totally 
neutral place in Cambodia or in a friendly country, I am honored 
to inform you as follows: 
  1. I have provided Samdech Chea Sim, Samdech Krompreah 
Norodom Ranariddh, and Samdech Hun Sen with the choice of the 
following two formulas: 
  In my opinion, the Party of Democratic Kampuchea [PDK] 
headed 
by yourself could be satisfied with the PDK delegation's 
residence in the Royal Palace near the Khemarin hall, which is 
presently occupied by His Excellency and Madam Khek Sisoda and 
Chinese doctors, who have agreed to move out of the building; 
  Or you want our roundtable meeting to be held in my 
residence 
at (Fang Sun-on) near Pyongyang in the DPRK. [as heard] 
  2. Samdech Chea Sim, Samdech Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh, 
and Samdech Hun Sen have just given me an unanimous answer that: 
  a. You will be staying in your office next to the Royal 
Palace, but outside the palace's perimeter. The three samdechs 
will guarantee 100 percent security for you and your PDK 
delegation during your stay in Phnom Penh for the round-table 
meeting. 
  3. The three samdechs object to your moving the roundtable 
meeting outside the Kingdom of Cambodia. 
  As for myself, I am of the opinion that if you disagree with 
the three samdechs on any aspect of the above formulas or have a 
contradictory request, our roundtable could be held in the 
future. Somehow, should you agree with the above formulas 
proposed by the three samdechs, our roundtable would take place 
as scheduled at the Damnak Chan pavilion in the Royal Palace in 
Phnom Penh from 2 to 7 May 1994. 
  Security guards to ensure security for you from Pochentong 
[Airport] to Phnom Penh and vice versa will be provided by the 
Kingdom of Cambodia's Royal Government. 
  Samdech Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh and Samdech Hun Sen, 
co-prime ministers of the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC], 
will be in charge of guaranteeing the security of you and your 
delegation during your stay in Phnom Penh. 
  Your Excellency, please accept my regards and deepest 
fidelity. 
  [Signed] Norodom Sihanouk 
  [Dated] Phnom Penh, 24 April 1994. 

</TEXT>

