<H3> <TI>   KR Fighting Continues in Battambang, Siem Reap </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KR Fighting Continues in Battambang, Siem Reap </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    More on Battambang, Pailin </H4>

<F P=102> BK2504003294 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2504003294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 0300 on 24 April, routed troops fleeing toward 
Treng quarreled and fired at one another, killing or wounding 
hundreds. Those who fled toward Battambang did so chaotically to 
save their lives. 
  On the battlefield east of Pailin: On 24 April we swept from 
O Kchheay to Chisang and completely controlled the area. We 
seized a T-54 tank and a tractor. 
  Special report: Preliminary results say that at 0020 on 23 
April, we launched a special attack against the regimental 
position of the communist Vietnamese puppets and the two-headed 
government in Sdau on Route 10, killing 19 on the spot, 
including a major. A number of soldiers were wounded and 
dragged back by their colleagues. We seized 10 assorted 
firearms. At 0300, their commanders ordered tanks to retake 
this position. However, so far no tanks have dared to show up. 

</TEXT>

