<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Said Killed, 35 Wounded in KR Train Ambush </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six Said Killed, 35 Wounded in KR Train Ambush </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2304120394 Hong Kong AFP in English 1133 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2304120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh, April 23 (AFP) -- Khmer Rouge [KR] 
guerrillas killed six people and injured 35 others when they 
ambushed a train running from the capital to Cambodia's second 
city of Battambang, the director of the state railway said 
Saturday. 
  "A group of about 40 Khmer Rouge laid six mines along the 
track and after the train hit the mines, they opened fire on the 
carriages," Pich Kimsreang, the railway director, said. 
  The engine was damaged and 11 coaches were derailed by the 
blast, he said. 
  The ambush took place Thursday in the Bakan district of 
western Pursat province, he added. 
  A firefight between the guerrillas and the railway militia 
went on for about an hour until the militia ran out of 
ammunition and ran to seek help from the local police or 
military, the director said. 
  "The Khmer Rouge then occupied the train for about five 
hours 
and robbed all the passengers. They took all the valuable 
belongings including 10 motorbikes," he said. 
  The guerrillas retreated when government forces arrived on 
the scene. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

