<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   District Town, Villages in Siem Reap `Liberated' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    District Town, Villages in Siem Reap `Liberated' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2604042494 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604042494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is a report from Route 68-western Siem Reap 
battlefield: 
  1. On 24 April, our forces attacked and completely liberated 
Angkor Chum District town. We seized a DK-75 and a DK-82. 
  2. Also on 24 April, we completely liberated Kouk Dong 
commune and 18 villages around this commune. We also completely 
liberated 12 villages in Nokor Pheas commune. 
  The people are very happy for having freed themselves from 
the claws of the archcriminals communist Vietnamese and 
two-headed government. Villagers have begun to till their lands 
for rice paddies. They are no longer forced to serve as puppet 
soldiers. 
  3. On the same day, we attacked the invading forces at 
Chongkal, killing two of them and wounding three others. 

</TEXT>

