<H3> <TI>   Nine Villages in Thmar Puok District `Liberated' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nine Villages in Thmar Puok District `Liberated' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2304090494 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2304090494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 21 April, the people, in cooperation with the 
National Army of Democratic Kampuchea, attacked and liberated 
Boeng Trakuon, Phnum Prak and Phnum Chhat areas, and the 
vicinity of Thmar Puok District. Moreover, the people also 
joined forces to liberate Kouk Romiet, Trayoeng, Kouk Prich, 
Kandaol, Thmei, Treas, Don Noy, Ta Soeng, and Sre L'ar villages, 
and so on. We destroyed four depots of armaments and 
ammunition; and we seized six warehouses of paddy that they had 
plundered from the people, a radio-communication 229-H, six 
field radios, 106 assorted guns, and some ammunition. 

</TEXT>

