<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Not To `Create' Economic Affairs Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Not To `Create' Economic Affairs Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2204080794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0759 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2204080794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 22 KYODO -- Japan's next coalition 
government will not create a new cabinet post in charge of 
coordinating economic affairs, a senior Trade Ministry official 
said Friday (922 April]. 
  The new cabinet expected to be inaugurated Monday under 
Tsutomu Hata, currently foreign minister in the government of 
outgoing Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa, will drop a plan to 
have an overall economics minister, said the official at the 
International Trade and Industry Ministry (MITI), who declined 
to be identified. 
  The creation of the post was suggested as a way to 
facilitate 
formulation of stimulus and other economic packages and help 
resolve Japan's trade difficulties with the United States. 

</TEXT>

