<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video; from the "NHK News" </F>
program] 
  [Text] A top official of the Japan Democratic Socialist 
Party [DSP], which is participating in the joint floor group 
"Kaishin," told reporters that even if the other coalition 
parties offer to reconsider the idea of forming "Kaishin" to ask 
the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] to return to the 
coalition, it believes that the SDPJ is no longer in a position 
