<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   LDP Expresses Sympathy With SDP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    LDP Expresses Sympathy With SDP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604103194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1027 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 26 KYODO -- The Liberal Democratic 
Party (LDP) on Tuesday urged the ruling coalition to hand over 
power to the opposition camp led by the LDP. 
  The LDP said in a statement that the ruling parties are to 
blame for the current situation of "political anarchy." 
  The statement, adopted at a meeting of all LDP members in 
the 
House of Representatives, expressed sympathy with the Social 
Democratic Party (SDP), which declared early Tuesday that it is 
quitting the coalition. 
  "The LDP, as a similar parliamentary political party, can 
understand the SDP's firm stand to bloc high-handed political 
management," the statement said. 
  Meanwhile, LDP President Yohei Kono told reporters that a 
major change has emerged in the coalition, saying "an insincere 
act was done to a coalition member." 
  "Is it okay to entrust the future of the people to such an 
insincere government which employs high-handed political 
methods? We cannot help but answer 'no'," Kono said. 
  The LDP joined the opposition camp last August after 38 
years 
of uninterrupted rule. 

</TEXT>

