<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Relations With Dominica Established </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diplomatic Relations With Dominica Established </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2404090494 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2404090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia has established diplomatic relations with 
the Commonwealth of Dominica at the ambassadorial level. A 
press statement issued by the Foreign Ministry in Jakarta today 
stated that the signing of the bilateral agreement to establish 
diplomatic relations was conducted in Washington on 19 April. A 
joint communique was signed by Indonesian ambassador to the 
United States Arifin Siregar and Dominica's ambassador to the 
United States (Eduard Wati), who represented their respective 
governments. 
  In his address, Ambassador Arifin Siregar, among other 
things, said that the establishment of diplomatic relations will 
further enhance bilateral cooperation in the fields of politics, 
economy, and culture between the two countries. According to 
Arifin Siregar, as developing nations, Indonesia and the 
Commonwealth of Dominica have a joint responsibility to 
establish a new world order which is free from strife, poverty, 
and injustice. 
  Meanwhile, in his address Ambassador (Eduard Wati) said that 
the Republic of Dominica should emulate Indonesia's fine example 
of development. 

</TEXT>

