<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Burmese Delegation Makes Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Burmese Delegation Makes Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Foreign Ministry Officials </H4>

<F P=102> BK2604094094 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, a delegation of our Lao Foreign 
Affairs Ministry led by Deputy Foreign Affairs Minister 
Phongsavat Bouppha held, in Vientiane, talks with a delegation 
of the Foreign Affairs Ministry of the Union of Myanmar [Burma] 
led by Deputy Foreign Affairs Minister U Nyunt Swe. The Myanmar 
Foreign Affairs Ministry delegation is currently on a visit to 
the Lao People's Democratic Republic [LPDR]. The visit is 
scheduled for 24 to 27 April. 
  In the talks, the two sides discussed the bilateral 
relations 
and cooperation in addition to exchanging views on various 
issues of common interest in the region and the world. They 
particularly discussed means to raise to a new, higher level the 
promotion and expansion of cooperation between the two countries 
in the economic, technical, scientific, and other fields to be 
worthy of being neighboring countries with mutual benefit. 
  U Maung Maung Lay, ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary of the Union of Myanmar to the LPDR, also 
attended the meeting on this occasion. 

</TEXT>

