<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Burmese Delegation Makes Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Burmese Delegation Makes Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Received by President, Foreign Minister </H4>

<F P=102> BK2604102994 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 0000 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, Nouhak Phoumsavan, president of our Lao 
People's Democratic Republic [LPDR], received at the Hokham 
Presidential Office in Vientiane a courtesy call from a Foreign 
Affairs Ministry delegation from the Union of Myanmar [Burma]. 
The delegation, headed by Deputy Foreign Affairs Minister U 
Nyunt Swe, is currently on a visit to the LPDR. The meeting 
between the guests and host proceeded in an atmosphere of warm 
cordiality. 
  The Myanmar deputy foreign affairs minister expressed thanks 
to President Nouhak Phoumsavan for the warm welcome. He also 
informed the president about the meeting and talks between the 
Foreign Affairs Ministry delegations of Myanmar and Laos, the 
meeting which, he said, marked a new step in the relations and 
cooperation in various fields between the two countries. U 
Nyunt Swe took the occasion to convey to President Nouhak 
Phoumsavan best wishes and warm greetings from General Than 
Shwe, chairman of the State Law and Order Restoration Council of 
the Union of Myanmar. The head of the Myanmar Foreign Affairs 
Ministry delegation also informed the president about the 
domestic situation in Myanmar, including the establishment of 
the new constitution. He also exchanged views with the 
president on the further promotion, expansion, and strengthening 
of the Myanmar-Lao relations. 
  President Nouhak Phoumsavan expressed a welcome to and 
highly 
appraised the visit to Laos by the Foreign Affairs Ministry 
delegation of the Union of Myanmar, a visit which he said marked 
a significant milestone in the promotion and expansion of the 
traditional, friendly relations and cooperation of good- 
neighborliness. He expressed the conviction that these 
relations between the two countries will be increasingly 
developed. 
  Earlier U Nyunt Swe and his delegation called on Somsavat 
Lengsavat, foreign affairs minister of the LPDR. The meeting 
proceeded in a cordial atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

