<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Heads Urge U.S. To Resume Dialogue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Party Heads Urge U.S. To Resume Dialogue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2504054294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0502 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il received solidarity messages from general 
secretary of the Central Committee of the All-Union Bolshevik 
Communist Party Nina Andreyeva, secretary general of the 
National Direction Committee of the Sudanese Union-African 
Democratic Rally in Mali Mamadou El Bechir Gologo and president 
of the Socialist Progressive Party of Lebanon Walid Jumblatt 
supporting the struggle of the Korean people to defend the 
dignity of the nation and sovereignty of the country. 
  The messages say the resumption of the "Team Spirit" joint 
military exercises and the deployment of Patriot missiles in 
South Korea pose a nuclear threat to the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea. 
  The messages urge the United States to give up at once its 
schemings to stifle Korea and resume dialogue with the DPRK 
without any condition. 
  They express firm support and solidarity for the resolute 
stand of the Korean people to safeguard the sovereignty and 
security of the country. 

</TEXT>

