<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hanchongnyon Vows `Anti-U.S.' Struggle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hanchongnyon Vows `Anti-U.S.' Struggle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2604050894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0500 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2604050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 26 (KCNA)--The South Korean 
Federation of General Student Councils (Hanchongnyon) called a 
press conference on the first anniversary of its inauguration on 
April 25 and vowed to wage a powerful anti-U.S., anti-Kim 
Yong-sam struggle, according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  The federation at the press conference noted that the Kim 
Yong-sam regime made many commitments when it set sail, but has 
fully revealed its anti-popular nature in the course of the 
Uruguay Round of the multilateral trade negotiations. It 
declared that it will launch an anti-U.S., anti-Kim Yong-sam 
struggle on the occasion of its first founding anniversary. 
  It said there is nothing to expect from the Kim Yong-sam 
regime which has clearly disclosed its color of a conservative 
"government". 

</TEXT>

