<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hanchongnyon Vows To Confront ROK Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204103894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1014 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Kim Hyon-chun, 
chairman of the South Korean Federation of General Student 
Councils (Hanchongnyon), at a recent press conference expressed 
the resolve of his federation to win in its confrontation with 
the pro-U.S. traitorous "government," a South Korean newspaper 
reported. 
  Noting that "Hanchongnyon at its congress of second-term 
representatives early this month branded the Kim Yong-sam regime 
as a pro-U.S. traitorous regime," Kim Hyon-chun said: "We will 
unite all people including the one million students under the 
slogan of independence, democracy and reunification and lay a 
foothold for victory in our confrontation with the Kim Yong-sam 
regime." 

</TEXT>

