<H3> <TI>   Report on Human Rights in ROK Cited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Report on Human Rights in ROK Cited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304110794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1027 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- An international 
organization affiliated with the U.N. Economic and Social 
Council and the Human Rights Information Centre under it in 
Moscow issued an information on the human rights situation in 
South Korea on April 7. 
  The information said despite the adoption of the agreement 
on 
reconciliation, nonaggression, cooperation and exchange between 
the North and the South, activities for national reunification 
are not only an entity of an acute political struggle but also a 
sphere of suppression of dissidents in South Korea. 
  Restrictive measures against national peace and 
reconciliation, free travel and contact between people with 
different ideologies must be revoked, said the information. 

</TEXT>

