<H3> <TI>   Agricultural Union Urges Reunification Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agricultural Union Urges Reunification Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304214994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1514 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- A spokesman of the 
Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Working People of 
Korea in a statement today demanded the South Korean authorities 
discard the wrong position of negating dialogue and pursuing war 
and show a positive response to the North-proposed convocation 
of a national conference, before it is too late. 
  The statement says: 
  The South Korean authorities block a wide-range dialogue 
involving various strata of society. This shows they do not want 
national reconciliation and unity, peace and reunification. It 
reveals their sinister political intention to isolate and stifle 
the Korean-style socialist system centred on the masses in 
conspiracy with outside forces. 
  The South Korean authorities must act with discretion, 
mindful that if they persistently refuse the proposed national 
conference and take the line of confrontation and war, they will 
face a grim judgement by the nation. 
  The Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Working 
People of Korea will continue to make all sincere efforts for 
the convocation of the national conference and remain faithful 
to its mission for the nation. 

</TEXT>

