<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hanminjon in Cuba Urges Ouster of Kim Yong-sam </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hanminjon in Cuba Urges Ouster of Kim Yong-sam </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2504055394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0514 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504055394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, April 23 (KCNA) -- Kim Chang-su, deputy 
chief of the mission of the South Korean National Democratic 
Front [SKNDF] (Hanminjon) in Cuba, at a press conference here on 
April 18 on the occasion of the 34th anniversary of the April 19 
popular uprising called upon the South Korean people to 
overthrow the Kim Yong-sam puppet regime and establish a 
democratic government. 
  He said the April 19, 1960, popular uprising in South Korea 
was a righteous resistance of the people who rose up in demand 
of a new politics, a new system and a new life against the 
colonial ruling system and fascist suppression by the U.S. 
imperialists and the Syngman Rhee puppet clique. 
  "The day is gone when the United States could model the 
world 
to its pleasure with strength and a strong arm," he said, and 
demanded: "The United States must squarely face the situation, 
immediately stop its adventurous war moves and get out of South 
Korea at once, taking along its forces and destruction weapons." 
  Denouncing the anti-reunification, anti-national and 
anti-popular crimes of the "civilian government", he said: "What 
Kim Yong-sam has done under the civilian mask eloquently proves 
that he is a truculent fascist dictator, splittist, sychophant 
traitor and warmaniac putting the preceding military dictators 
in the shade". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

