<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reunification Group Chairman Praises Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reunification Group Chairman Praises Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2604011094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2157 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2604011094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- "Our motherland under 
the wise guidance of the great leader Generalissimo Kim Il-song 
and the dear leader Marshal Kim Chong-il is making a long drive 
as a powerful country," said Chu Yong-il, vice-chairman of the 
International Federation of Koreans for Reunification. 
  He told KCNA: 
  "I deem it a great honor and pleasure to have had an 
opportunity to visit the homeland and celebrate the birthday of 
the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song. Seeing the motherland 
prospering, I feel my heart swell with pride in being a member 
of the Korean nation. 
  "Thanks to our great leader and dear leader, my motherland 
has greeted prosperity without precedent in its history of five 
thousand years and become the most dignified country in the 
world. 
  "There is no such person as the great leader Comrade Kim 
Il-song who has devoted everything to the people all his life, 
regarding `believing in the people as in heaven' as his motto. 
He has led our people to be the happiest and most proud and 
intelligent people. Our motherland owes its singlehearted unity 
to this care shown by him. 
  "The building of an independent national economy, the 
embodiment of the chuche idea in the economy, has brought about 
a dazzling development of our motherland today and it has served 
as an unshakable foundation which is not affected by any 
worldwide economic fluctuation and threat from the imperialists." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

