<H3> <TI>   Letter Proposes 15 Aug North-South Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Letter Proposes 15 Aug North-South Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2604012794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2227 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2604012794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The North side has 
recently sent a letter, which contains the proposal to convene a 
national conference in Pyongyang or Seoul around the forthcoming 
August 15 to seek a way for great unity of the whole Korean 
nation, by international mail to the South Korean authorities, 
political parties, organizations, individual figures and 
overseas Koreans. 
  The proposal was adopted at a joint meeting of the DPRK 
Government, political parties and public organizations on April 
11. 
  The letter was sent to the South Korean authorities, 
representatives of the "Democratic Liberal Party", the 
Democratic Party, the United People's Party, the "New Korea 
Party" and the New Political Reform Party, representatives of 
workers', peasants' and students' organizations, representatives 
of educational, cultural, press, religious and reunification 
movement organisations and other organisations, and figures of 
business and other circles. 
  It was also mailed to the chairman, the vice-chairmen and 
the 
secretary general of the overseas headquarters of the National 
Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminnyon), chairmen 
of Pomminnyon regional headquarters, the co-chairman and the 
co-secretary general of the Alliance of Youths and Students for 
the Country's Reunification, the chairman and the advisor of the 
International Federation of Koreans for Reunification, the 
chairman of the Committee of Korean Veterans in Moscow, the 
president of the International Taekwon-do Federation and other 
overseas Koreans. 

</TEXT>

