<F P=102>   SK2604075894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2100 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2604075894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2100 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Seoul's Christian Broadcasting System 
reports, on 25 April the Kim Yong-sam puppet clique launched the 
provocative Hwarang war exercise in Inchon and the areas of 
Kyonggi Province adjacent to the military demarcation line. 
  The exercise in which some 1.3 million puppet military 
personnel, police officers, and reservists are taking part will 
be conducted for five days under the pretext of defending the 
homeland and facilities against someone's infiltration. 
  The war exercise commotion perpetrated by the puppet clique 
is all the more adventurous since it is staged right after 
warmonger U.S. Defense Secretary Perry left Seoul after hatching 
a war plot and, in particular, is timed to coincide with the 
deployment of the latest-type Patriot missiles. 
  The prevailing situation once again exposes the fact that 
the 
Kim Yong-sam regime has completely thrown away its civilian 
mask, has clearly revealed its color as a warmonger, and is 
kicking up its preparations for a northward invasion. 

</TEXT>

