<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Koreans in Japan Meet on `U.S. War Moves' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2504062194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0527 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504062194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 23 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] -- 
An emergency meeting of Koreans in Japan against the U.S. war 
moves took place in Tokyo on April 17. 
  It was co-sponsored by the Alliance of South Koreans in 
Japan 
for Democracy and Unification, the South Korean Youth League in 
Japan and the Democratic Association of South Korean Women in 
Japan. 
  The resolution adopted at the meeting urges the United 
States 
to give up the scheme to resume the "Team Spirit" military 
exercises and stop deploying Patriot missiles and other weapons 
of mass destruction in South Korea under the pretext of the 
"nuclear issue" and hold the third round of talks with North 
Korea at an early date and resolve all the outstanding problems 
between the two countries in a peaceful way in a package deal. 
  It demands that the Kim Yong-sam regime renounce the policy 
of confrontation with the North and dependence on foreign forces 
and choose the road of national reconciliation and reunification 
by maintaining independence and that the Japanese Government 
seek a negotiated solution to the "nuclear issue," instead of 
following the U.S. war policy. 

</TEXT>

