<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Media, Events Observe KPA Founding Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Media, Events Observe KPA Founding Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Yi In-mo Visits Unit </H4>

<F P=102> SK2504060694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0520 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504060694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Yi In-mo, a former war 
correspondent of the Korean People's Army [KPA], who is known as 
an incarnation of faith and will, visited the Yim Chang-sun unit 
of the Korean People's Army together with his family on April 23 
to congratulate the soldiers on the 62nd founding anniversary of 
the People's Army and present souvenirs to them. 
  Witnessing the great might of the People's Army which defies 
comparison with that 40 odd years ago, Yi expressed deep 
reverence for Comrade Kim Chong-il, supreme commander, who has 
built an invincible army which no formidable enemy dare provoke. 
  Recalling that the enemy in South Korea put him to all sorts 
of tortures to convert him, but could not bring him to his 
knees, Yi said: 
  "I fought till victory with the conviction that I would win 
surely, as there was for me the great General Kim Il-song. 
  "Touring different places of the socialist motherland, I was 
charmed by the great idea and guidance of the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il for the country and the people. 
  "We will certainly win because the dear leader is with us. 
  "Let all of us defend general Kim Chong-il with our lives." 
  Yi In-mo wrote in the unit's combat register: "Let us be 
rifles and bombs defending general Kim Chong-il, the greatest 
general in the world, with death." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7041 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas080_c_94033" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-080 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Media, Events Observe KPA Founding Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Media, Events Observe KPA Founding Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Leaders Visit Army Unit </H4>

<F P=102> SK2504235494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2238 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504235494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il, chairman of the 
National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic 
of Korea and Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army 
[KPA], today visited the Unit 564 of the Korean People's Army 
and congratulated officers and men there on the occasion of the 
62nd anniversary of the founding of the heroic Korean People's 
Army. 
  The officers and men of the unit warmly welcomed President 
Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il, raising thunderous cheers 
of "hurrah !". 
  President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il were 
presented 
with bunches of flowers carrying boundless reverence of the 
entire KPA officers and men. 
  President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il were greeted 
on the spot by O Chin-u, first vice-chairman of the DPRK 
National Defence Commission and Minister of People's Armed 
Forces; Choe Kwang, vice-chairman of the DPRK National Defence 
Commission and Chief of General Staff of the Korean People's 
Army; Yi Ul-sol, Kim Pong-yul and Kim Kwang-chin, members of the 
DPRK National Defence Commission and vice marshals of the Korean 
People's Army; Vice Marshals of the KPA Choe In-tok, Paek 
Hak-nim and Kim Ik-hyon; generals of the KPA Yi Ha-il, Kim 
Tu-nam, Yi Pong-won and Kim Myong- kuk; and other generals of 
the KPA and commanding officers of the Army unit. 
  President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il warmly 
congratulated the KPA officers and men on the 62nd founding 
anniversary of the KPA and met soldiers to acquaint themselves 
with their life in the Army. 
  They noted with deep satisfaction that the People's Army, 
forming an integrated whole with the party and the leader, was 
successfully discharging its honorable duty and mission as a 
reliable defender of the revolutionary cause of chuche, the 
cause of socialism, and encouraged the soldiers of the Army unit 
who were firmly preparing themselves as a-match-for-a-hundred 
combatants. 
  President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il posed for a 
souvenir picture with the officers and men of the unit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

