<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting of Coal Industry Functionaries Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meeting of Coal Industry Functionaries Held </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Participants Commended </H4>

<F P=102> SK2304044894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0428 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- High citations of the 
state and gifts were awarded to the participants in the national 
meeting of coal industrial workers which was held in Pyongyang 
from April 20 to 22. 
  The title of labour hero of the DPRK were awarded to nine 
participants, citations of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song to 16, citations of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il 
to 86, the title of merited coal miner to 31, the Order of 
National Flag first class to 62, the Labour Order to 480, the 
Order of National Flag second class to 821 and the Order of 
National Flag third class to 814 at the awarding ceremony on 
April 22. 
  Testimonials of President Kim Il-song were awarded to 390 
and 
gifts of Comrade Kim Chong-il to the entire participants of the 
meeting. 
  The speakers at the awarding ceremony said that the 
commendation was a token of deep political trust and benevolent 
love of President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il who 
always reared the coal miners in their warm bosoms and put them 
in the foreground. 
  They vowed to overfulfil the coal production plan for the 
period of adjustment in order to repay this solicitude with 
loyalty. 

</TEXT>

