<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-080 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting of Coal Industry Functionaries Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meeting of Coal Industry Functionaries Held </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Officials Attend Award Ceremony </H4>

<F P=102> SK2304060794 Pyongyang Korean Central Television Network in 
Korean 1100 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2304060794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A ceremony to grant official commendations and 
gifts from Comrade Kim Il-song, the great leader of our party 
and people, and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il to the 
participants of the national meeting of functionaries of the 
coal industry was held at the People's Palace of Culture on 22 
April. 
  Present at the meeting were Comrade Yi Chong-ok [member of 
the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) Political Bureau and vice 
president], Comrade Choe Yong-nim, Comrade Hong Song-nam 
[candidate members of the WPK Political Bureau and vice premiers 
of the Administration Council], Comrade Hong Sok-hyong 
[candidate member of the WPK Political Bureau and chairman of 
the State Planning Commission], functionaries concerned, and 
exemplary functionaries and miners of the coal industry from all 
over the country. 
  After a decree of the DPRK Central People's Committee was 
read, the title of labor hero of the DPRK was awarded to nine 
participants, including Hungnyong coal mine manager Ho Yun-chan. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

