<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister on Cambodian Border Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister on Cambodian Border Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2604102794 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaking in an interview with newsmen at Government 
House this morning, Defense Minister General Wichit Sukmak said 
the Defense and Foreign Ministries are working together in 
compiling data on Cambodian intrusions, spillover fighting, and 
casualties suffered by Thai people living along the Cambodian 
border. Asked whether the military would hand over directly to 
the United Nations the evidence collected by Thailand, Gen. 
Wichit said the armed forces would let the Foreign Ministry do 
that by taking into consideration the impact on Thai-Cambodian 
relations. 
  [Begin recording] [Wichit] The Foreign Ministry will decide 
which information can be used and whether the political 
situation is appropriate for us to make a protest -- whether the 
good relations would be affected. The Foreign Ministry will 
decide about that, but we are ready to provide it with facts. 
  [Unidentified reporter] To improve the situation, do you 
think the supreme commander should make a visit there? 
  [Wichit] We must try to preserve and promote relations 
between our two countries since we are neighbors. That's what 
we should do. Especially the military, we must try promote good 
relations. There is fighting in Cambodia, and we must work 
together in order to prevent spillover into Thailand. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

