<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rice, Crop Varieties Protection Law To Be Drafted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rice, Crop Varieties Protection Law To Be Drafted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2304104394 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2304104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Department of Intellectual Property has been 
entrusted to draft a legislation for the protection of rice and 
other crop varieties. Deputy Commerce Minister Churin 
Laksanawisit says when the legislation takes effect, other 
people will not be allowed to make use of the rice and other 
crop varieties without consent of the owner who obtains specific 
varieties through cross breeding. Mr. Churin says the 
legislation will prevent other countries from taking Thai rice 
varieties to be further developed in their countries to enable 
them to become Thailand's major competitors for rice exports. 
  He says Vietnam has a policy to promote the cultivation of 
Hom Mali variety because of better prices it fetches compared 
with other varieties. However, the country has been faced with 
the problem of plant diseases; therefore, its Hom Mali output is 
still unsatisfactory. 
  Mr. Churin says Thailand and Vietnam have already concluded 
a 
memorandum of understanding on cooperation in rice exports. 
Both countries will later hold consultations on prices of rice 
exports. They may set the median price to avoid price 
undercutting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7056 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas080_m_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-080 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

