<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ramos To Expand East ASEAN Growth Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ramos To Expand East ASEAN Growth Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2604033994 Manila BUSINESS WORLD in English 21 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> BK2604033994 </F>
<F P=104>  Manila BUSINESS WORLD </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Ramos has approved the adoption of 
several measures aimed at accelerating the implementation of the 
Brunei Darussalam, Indonesia, Malaysia, Philippines-East ASEAN 
Growth Area (BIMP-EAGA), reporters learned yesterday. 
  During the Cabinet meeting last Tuesday, the president 
directed the immediate establishment of a Philippine council to 
pursue the implementation of the BIMP-EAGA. He also ordered 
various government agencies to undertake activities for the 
operationalization of the EAGA and to identify additional 
flagship development projects in Mindanao to support the same. 
  To boost awareness and speed up implementation, Mr. Ramos 
likewise ordered the creation of additional investment and 
tourism promotion councils (ITPCs) in major cities of Mindanao 
to conduct awareness campaign on the BIMP-EAGA. 
  Currently, there are ITPCs in Davao, Zamboanga, and Cagayan 
de Oro. The additional councils will be located in Cotabato, 
Gen. Santos, Butuan, and Iligan. 
  The EAGA was formally launched last March in Davao City. 

</TEXT>

