<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   NDF Anniversary Marred by Widening Rift </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NDF Anniversary Marred by Widening Rift </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2604041694 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2604041694 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A communist movement in the Philippines, the 
National Democratic Front [NDF] celebrated its 21st anniversary, 
Sunday, but reports saying the rift within the communist 
movement is expanding as more statements were issued by factions 
in observance of the group's anniversary. A spokesperson for 
two breakaway communist factions in Mindanao in southern 
Philippines said groups who oppose the leadership of exiled 
communist leader Jose Maria Sison have been branded by forces 
loyal to him as counter-revolutionaries. 
  Ike de los Reyes, speaking for NDF Central Mindanao and the 
Moro Revolutionary Army said, members of the breakaway groups 
now fear liquidation not only by the military but also by former 
comrades who still acknowledge Sison's leadership. Europe based 
critics of Sison also said a statement declaring they now 
represent the real NDF indicating that the rift have extended to 
the continent. Sison is himself exiled in the Utrecth, 
Netherlands. 

</TEXT>

