<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seoul, Moscow Agree on Exchange of Embassy Lands </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seoul, Moscow Agree on Exchange of Embassy Lands </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2104121294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1129 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2104121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 21 (YONHAP) -- South Korea and Russia 
have agreed to mutually furnish the same size of embassy lands 
with South Korea additionally paying to Russia a cash 
compensation for the land of the former Tsarist Russian legation 
in Seoul. 
  A Foreign Ministry official said on Thursday that under the 
agreement, the two countries will mutually furnish embassy lots 
extending 7,920 square meters. 
  The cash compensation Korea will pay to Russia will be 12 
million dollars, he said. 
  "We arrived at the agreement in recent negotiations made 
based on Seoul's promise last August that Korea would properly 
compensate for the land of the former Russian legation," he said. 
  The land Korea will obtain from Russia would be in Moscow's 
diplomatic estate and Korea will provide Russia with a land in 
downtown Seoul, the official added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

