<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul yesterday welcomed the inauguration of the new 
Japanese government led by Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Chang Ki-ho hoped, in a 
commentary, that South Korea and Japan, sharing common values 
and ideology, will further strengthen friendly and cooperative 
ties while the new Japanese government is in office. 
  "We expect South Korea and Japan to be able to build a new 
dimension of cooperative relations in preparation for the coming 
21st century," and Chang. 
  He also praised Hata's predecessor, Morihiro Hosokawa, for 
his efforts to promote bilateral relations between South Korea 
and Japan. 

