<H3> <TI>   President To Visit Indonesia for First Time </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President To Visit Indonesia for First Time </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    VNA Previews Visit </H4>

<F P=102> BK2604091594 Hanoi VNA in English 0641 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2604091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 26 -- President Le Duc Anh's first 
visit to Indonesia which begins on April 26 is of significant 
importance, marking a new milestone in the friendly and 
cooperative relations between Vietnam and Indonesia, and making 
active contributions to building Southeast Asia into a region of 
peace, stability, friendship and cooperation, says QUAN DOI NHAN 
DAN paper in a editorial today. The army paper expresses 
pleasure at the time- honoured friendship and cooperation 
between Vietnam and Indonesia. After lauding the all-sided 
achievements of the Indonesian people in national construction 
and defence, the paper says as chairman of the Non-Aligned 
Movement Indonesia is actively working for the unity and growth 
of Vietnam following the exchange of visit between delegations 
of their government and armies, especially those by President 
Suharto in November 1990, the first Vietnam visit by an 
Indonesia president in many decades, and Prime Minister Vo Van 
Kiet's visit to Indonesia in November 1991, President Le Duc 
Anh's visit to Indonesia this time will open a new page in the 
fine relationship between the two countries, the paper concludes. 

</TEXT>

