<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Groups Assail U.S. Actions on Peninsula </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Groups Assail U.S. Actions on Peninsula </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304111794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1051 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- Political parties and 
organisations of various countries denounced moves of the U.S. 
imperialists against the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  The Central Committee of the African Party of Independence 
of 
Senegal in a statement April 7 said the United States totally 
reversed the agreed conclusions reached at the DPRK-USA contact 
in New York and was going to resume the "Team Spirit" joint 
military exercises and deployed "Patriot" missiles in South 
Korea. 
  A statement published by the participants in the 
international chuche idea seminar on independence, peace and 
friendship on April 10 denounced the U.S. imperialists for 
massing their huge Armed Forces in South Korea and around the 
Korean peninsula, vociferating about the resumption of the "Team 
Spirit" joint military exercises, and branded it as a brazen 
violation of the sovereignty and dignity of the Korean people 
and as an act of provocation to stifle the socialism of Korea. 
  It urged the United States to cancel the plan to resume the 
"Team Spirit" joint military exercises that poses a big threat 
to peace and security on the Korean peninsula and in the Far 
East. "If the U.S. imperialists and the reactionaries take the 
road of unleashing another war on the Korean peninsula, we, 
together with the followers of the chuche idea all over the 
world, will fight on the same trench with the Korean people with 
arms in hand," the statement stressed. 
  The Mozambican Committee for Friendship with the People of 
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in a statement on 
April 6 said that the United States must immediately stop its 
moves to stifle the system of socialist Korea and renounce its 
policy hostile to it, and the United Nations Security Council 
and the International Atomic Energy Agency must not follow the 
United States any longer, discarding the double standard and 
partiality. 
  The Denmark-Democratic People's Republic of Korea Friendship 
Association in a statement said the U.S. clamor about "nuclear 
threat from North Korea" is completely groundless. The nuclear 
issue of the Korean peninsula can be resolved only when all the 
nuclear weapons of the United States are removed from South 
Korea and such aggressive war exercises as "Team Spirit" stopped 
and all the U.S. forces withdrawn from there, the statement 
stressed. 

</TEXT>

