<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Demands Japan Halt `Hostile Policy' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Demands Japan Halt `Hostile Policy' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304055894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0436 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304055894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 21 [dateline as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- 
The Central Standing Committee of the General Association of 
Korean residents in Japan (Chongnyon) strongly demanded that the 
Japanese Govermnent authorities immediately stop the hostile 
policy toward the Democratic People's Republic of Korea which 
they are pursuing in conspiracy with the United States and the 
South Korean authorities. 
  Paek Han-ki, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee 
of Chongnyon, released a statement of the Chongnyon Central 
Standing Committee at a press conference in Tokyo on April 21. 
  On April 19, gangsters of a Japanese rightwing organisation 
thronged to the central headquarters of Chongnyon and cried 
"Koreans, get out of Japan" and "Chongnyon, get out of Japan". 
On the same day, a similar rowdyism was staged by scores of 
loudspeaker cars of the rightwing organisation in front of the 
buildings of the Federation of Korean Credit Associations in 
Japan and the Tonghae Trading Company. 
  On April 14, a schoolgirl of the Tokyo Korean middle and 
high 
school was beaten on the head by an unidentified man in a 
tramcar. Such cases of violence are frequently reported from 
various parts of Japan. 
  The statement said the responsibility for these cases rested 
with the Japanese Government authorities who have pursued a 
hostile policy toward the DPRK and incited hatred for the Korean 
residents in Japan, while strengthening the "cooperation system" 
of the United States, Japan and South Korea under the pretext of 
fictitious "nuclear issue of the North". 
  "The current trend in which they foster persecution of the 
Korean residents in Japan, spreading unfounded rumours, reminds 
us of the eve of the great earthquake of 1923 in Kanto district 
after which Koreans were massacred," the statement said, and 
added: 
  "We demand that the Japanese Government authorities promptly 
renounce their hostile policy toward the DPRK and take measures 
to prevent recurrence of outrages by rightwing gangsters and 
that some media stop unwarrantable anti-DPRK propaganda and 
prejudiced reporting that incites chauvinism." 

</TEXT>

