<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rengo's Yamagishi Predicts Dissolution of Diet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rengo's Yamagishi Predicts Dissolution of Diet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804021294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 27 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2804021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Three top executives of Rengo [Japanese Trade Union 
Confederation] held an emergency meeting in Atami city, Shizuoka 
Prefecture, on 26 April. Following the secession of the Social 
Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] from the coalition, they 
confirmed Rengo's policy of deciding whether or not to cooperate 
with Hata's new administration "on a case-by-case basis, based 
on policy." In a news conference, Rengo Chairman Akira 
Yamagishi said: "If a minority ruling group is formed without 
the SDPJ, it will be impossible to manage the political 
situation in a normal manner. While it is not good to conduct an 
election under the multiple-seat constituency system which was 
`pronounced dead,' the Diet is likely to be dissolved soon." He 
thus predicted there is a possibility of Diet dissolution under 
the present multiple-seat constituency system after passage of 
the 1994 budget bill. 

</TEXT>

