BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 26 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The Vice 
Minister of Infrastructure Development T. Damiran said in his 
interview to the governmental newspaper "DZASGIYN GADZRYN MEUEE" 
that in the current year it is scheduled to allot some 6 billion 
tugrik for capital investment in the sphere of construction at 
the expense of the state centralized budget. This sum is 
exceeding by 2 billion tugrik the last year's ones. T. Damiran 
noted that including the means of aimags' budgets, enterprises 
and economic entities privately-owned the total volume of 
capital investment in the construction constitutes this year 
some 16 billion tugrik. At the same time the vice minister 
underscored that the growing amount of capital investment should 
be understood in connection with the inflation that is to say 
the actual volume of construction is not to exceed the last 
year's taking into consideration all the means allotted it is 
expected that more than 500 objects are to be made available in 
the current year. As was informed by the vice minister, at 
present in the sphere of construction there are working some 20 
thousand qualified construction workers and additionally some 15 
thousand seasonal ones. In accordance with the contracts 
concluded there are about one thousand Russian workers engaged 
in the construction sphere as well. According to the latest 
statistics, there were about 60 thousand qualified workers 
engaged in the construction industry of Mongolia up to 1990. 

</TEXT>

