<H3> <TI>   Keating: Facilities Planned in Papua New Guinea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Keating: Facilities Planned in Papua New Guinea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2404121794 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 1100 GMT 
24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2404121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Australia is putting $1.5 million towards new 
facilities at (Kakoda) in Papua New Guinea [PNG]. The prime 
minister, Paul Keating, says Australia and the PNG Government 
will jointly build facilities expected to include a new airport 
terminal and a medical center. Mr. Keating says the facilities 
will commemorate the sacrifices made by both countries during 
bloody Second World War battles with Japanese forces. He has 
paid tribute to Australian personnel who served at (Kakoda) and 
praised the unquestioning help, courage, and selfless 
humanitarianism of Papua New Guineans. 

</TEXT>

