<H3> <TI>   CNN Vice President Sends Thanks to Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNN Vice President Sends Thanks to Kim Il-song </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304060494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0505 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304060494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received a letter of thanks from Eason 
Jordan, senior vice president of CNN, who had visited the DPRK 
together with former heads of state and government and 
politicians of different countries. 
  Expressing thanks to President Kim Il-song for welcoming CNN 
to the DPRK, the letter dated April 19 says: 
  Our visit was a memorable one, with the high point our 
meeting with you on April 16th. 
  At the beginning of our trip, I wrote to you to reaffirm 
CNN's commitment to fair, balanced and objective coverage of the 
DPRK. After a week of reporting here, including a live broadcast 
from DPRK TV, I hope you will agree that we have maintained 
those high standards. In addition, I hope our reports have made 
some contribution to greater international understanding of your 
country and to the cause of world peace. 
  With this visit, I hope we have laid the groundwork for a 
long-term, positive and mutually beneficial relationship 
qbetween CNN and the DPRK. We stand ready to return to 
Pyongyang at any time when warranted by important news 
developments, and we hope your government will continue to give 
positive consideration to our requests to travel here. 
  Again, many thanks for all you have done to help us. 

</TEXT>

