<H3> <TI>   CNN, Japan's NHK Thank Kim Chong-il </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNN, Japan's NHK Thank Kim Chong-il </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2304110594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1006 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il received letters of thanks from the senior 
vice-president of the U.S. CNN and the Japanese NHK news 
coverage group that had visited Korea with former heads of state 
and government and politicians of different countries. 
  The letters dated April 19 expressed sincere thanks to 
Comrade Kim Chong-il for inviting them to visit and report on 
the DPRK. 
  Senior Vice-President of the U.S. CNN Eason Jordan in his 
letter of thanks said; "Our visit was extremely successful, 
especially our meeting and coverage of President Kim Il-song. 
We owe a great debt of gratitude to you". 
  He hoped that through coverage and report the CNN has made 
some contribution to international understanding of Korea and to 
the cause of world peace and laid the groundwork for a long-term 
and positive relationship with Korea. 
  The letter expressed once again thanks to consideration and 
support of Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  The Japanese NHK news coverage group in the letter of thanks 
said that the invitation of the NHK coverage group representing 
Japan and CNN coverage group representing the United States 
under the present rigorous situation surrounding the Korean 
peninsula today was made by the wise decision of Comrade Kim 
Chong-il. 
  The letter continues: 
  As the old saying goes, "seeing is believing." The true 
looks 
of the DPRK which no one can know without visiting it and 
meeting people have been conveyed to the world, I believe. 
  NHK will in the future, too, make efforts for the 
improvement 
of the DPRK-Japan relations and for peace and prosperity of 
Northeast Asia on the basis of the deep cooperative relations 
with the DPRK hitherto. 
  The letter hoped that Comrade Kim Chong-il would understand 
such a stance of report of NHK and give guidance for the 
establishment of eternal relations between NHK and the DPRK. It 
sincerely wished President Kim Il-song and Secretary Kim 
Chong-il good health and a long life. 

</TEXT>

