<H3> <TI>   Pomminnyon Urges ROK To Accept Conference Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pomminnyon Urges ROK To Accept Conference Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2804103394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1022 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2804103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["South Side's Authorities Urged To Accept North's Proposal </F>
for National Conference" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 28 (KCNA) -- The preparatory 
committee for the formation of the South side headquarters of 
the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification 
(Pomminnyon) strongly urged the South side authorities to accept 
the proposal for the convocation of a national conference, a 
proposal initiated by the DPRK at a joint meeting of its 
government, political parties and public organizations on April 
11 with a view to finding a way of achieving the great unity of 
the whole nation. 
  In a document distributed on April 15 it charged that the 
Kim 
Yong-sam "government" deepened the national division by refusing 
even to accept the proposal of the North, without so much as 
showing an attitude to sincerely examine it. 
  Noting that the crisis of the nation cannot be defused, nor 
can the way of an independent and peaceful reunification of the 
country be opened by such mode of dependence on outside forces 
as "South Korea-U.S.-Japan cooperation", the document stressed 
the only way is to activate diverse dialogues of all levels 
including dialogue between the government authorities and thus 
boost the sentiments of great national unity and find an 
independent solution. 
  It repeatedly urged the South Korean authorities to accept 
the proposal of the North for a national conference. 

</TEXT>

