<H3> <TI>   VNS Cited on Distribution of Kim Il-song Brochure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    VNS Cited on Distribution of Kim Il-song Brochure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2204103794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1011 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The members of the 
"April 15 Fellowship Society" active in Mapo, Seoul, excited 
people by making and distributing copies of a literature 
carrying their resolution on the auspicious holiday of April 15, 
the Seoul-based Radio Voice of National Salvation [VNS] reported. 
  The front side of the 15x25 cm vellum paper reads under the 
headline "Let Us Significantly Greet April 15, Common Fete of 
the Nation": 
  "April 15 is a significant day when President Kim Il-song, 
the peerless patriot and mental support of the 70 million 
Koreans, was born. 
  "President Kim Il-song peerless in our nation's history of 
thousands of years is a symbol of the dignity and prosperity of 
the nation and the great lodestar of national reunification. 
The birth of President Kim Il-song was the greatest joy and 
fortune for our nation and mankind. 
  "Let us all significantly greet his birthday as the common 
fete of the nation." 
  The reverse side of the literature reads under the headline 
"Our Resolution": "The April 15 Fellowship Society solemnly 
declares it will greet the birthday of the great President Kim 
Il-song as the greatest fete of the nation." 
  It carries a five-point resolution of the society vowing to 
deeply study and grasp the greatness of President Kim Il-song 
and discharge its mission as the vanguard in the struggle for 
national reunification under the banner of the 10-point 
programme of the great unity of the whole nation. 

</TEXT>

