  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il received a solidarity message from Nina 
Andreyeva, general secretary of the Central Committee of the 
All-Union Bolshevik Communist Party, on the second anniversary 
of the publication of the Pyongyang declaration. 
  The solidarity message dated April 14 says the declaration 
is 
of particular significance in the struggle to defend and advance 
the cause of socialism and in strengthening the unity and 
solidarity of the international communist and working-class 
movements. 
  It further says: 
  The All-Union Bolshevik Communist Party calls for the full 
achievement of the aim and principles of the Pyongyang 
declaration and it is conducting activities to check the return 
to capitalism and reconstruct the Union of Soviet Socialist 
Republics. 
