<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Pyongyang Declaration Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of Pyongyang Declaration Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Russia, Peru Observe Anniversary </H4>

<F P=102> SK2304110394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1020 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304110394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- The second anniversary 
of the publication of the Pyongyang declaration "Let Us Defend 
and Advance the Cause of Socialism" was observed in Peru and 
Russia. 
  The declaration was adopted in April 1992 by leaders and 
representatives of political parties advocating socialism who 
came to Pyongyang to celebrate the 80th birthday of the great 
leader President Kim Il-song. 
  Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of 
Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, made a speech at a 
meeting held at the front on April 13. 
  He said it is only two years since the adoption of the 
Pyongyang declaration, but more than 200 parties have signed it 
and its vitality is growing day by day. 
  "The Pyongyang declaration, which clarified the superiority 
of socialism to capitalism, the inevitability of the victory of 
socialism and the tasks and ways of defending and advancing 
socialism, has served as a weapon for the socialists in their 
struggle," he said, adding that his front which also signed the 
declaration would resolutely fight to defend and advance the 
cause of socialism. 
  In his speech at a meeting with representatives of Russian 
political parties held in Moscow April 20, V.I. Anpilov, 
secretary of the Central Committee of the Russian Communist 
Workers' Party, said "the Pyongyang declaration is the hope of 
our cause and the beacon of socialism for the communists." "In 
the struggle for socialism," he continued, "the Workers' Party 
of Korea and its leaders Comrade Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim 
Chong-il show an example." 
  A.A. Rapin, secretary of the Central Committee of the 
All-Union Bolshevik Communist Party, in his speech said the 
Pyongyang declaration opened a new high stage in the development 
of the international communist movement and the working-class 
movement. "This declaration will be recorded in history along 
with the `communist manifesto'," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

