<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Pyongyang Declaration Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of Pyongyang Declaration Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Foreign Parties Lend Support </H4>

<F P=102> SK2304112094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1037 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- Leaders of political 
parties of different countries expressed full support to and 
sympathy with "Let Us Defend and Advance the Cause of 
Socialism", the Pyongyang declaration published in Pyongyang in 
April 1992. 
  Branko Kitanovic, general secretary of the New Yugoslav 
Communist Movement, said that delegates of many communist and 
workers' parties and political parties of many countries 
aspiring after socialism gathered in Pyongyang and declared to 
the whole world that they would struggle for the victory of 
socialism, and this was a historical event which marked a new 
milestone in the strengthening and development of the socialist 
and communist movement. 
  The Pyongyang declaration, he said, serves the communists 
and 
progressive peoples of the world as a common fighting program in 
rebuilding the socialist and communist movement and advancing 
the cause of socialism with a clear fighting goal on a new basis 
after socialism has suffered a setback and capitalism has 
revived in East European countries owing to moves of the 
renegades of revolution. 
  Guillermo Garcia Ponce, general secretary of the "New 
Alternative" of Venezuela, in a statement issued to the press 
said the Pyongyang declaration is an inspiring banner which gave 
firm confidence in victory to the revolutionary parties and 
people of the world aspiring after socialism, and it declared to 
the whole world that the victory of the socialist cause is 
inevitable. 
  Guzman Rivera Castaneda, general secretary of the 
Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru, said the Pyongyang 
declaration is a fine document which dealt a telling blow at the 
imperialists who were resorting to vicious anti- communist 
rackets, making a bluff. 
  Sean Garland, member of the Central Executive Committee of 
the Workers' Party of Ireland, said the Pyongyang declaration is 
the source of unity of all the progressive forces. The fact 
that more than 200 revolutionary parties and progressive 
political parties of the world signed the declaration fully 
proves its great vitality, he added. 
  Ludo Martens, chairman of the Central Committee of the 
Belgian Labour Party, said the Pyongyang declaration is a solemn 
declaration announcing a new start of the communist movement. 
The just cause of the revolutionary parties of the world who 
are advancing under the banner of this declaration is sure to be 
crowned with victory, he stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

