<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Celebration of Kim Il-song Birthday </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Celebration of Kim Il-song Birthday </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Foreign Countries Mark Day </H4>

<F P=102> SK2204105994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1033 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2204105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- A national seminar on 
the chuche idea was held in Helsinki on the occasion of the 
birthday of the great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  Pekka Rantala, chairman of the Finnish National Committee 
for 
the Study of the Chuche Idea, made a report, followed by 
speeches. 
  They noted that President Kim Il-song authored the chuche 
idea during the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and has 
applied it in all fields of the revolution and construction and 
built Korea to be a model country of socialism as today. 
  They said Korea is making a great progress in the revolution 
and construction under the banner of socialism, not wavering in 
face of the pressure and provocations of the imperialists, 
because it is guided by the chuche idea authored by President 
Kim Il-song. 
  The chuche idea now serves as the undisputed guiding idea in 
the building of socialism and communism and the most universal 
guiding idea from which the world people learn, they added. 
  A congratulatory message to President Kim Il-song was 
adopted 
at the seminar. 
  DPRK book, photo and handicraft exhibitions and film shows 
for April 15 took place in Montevideo, Uruguay, Almada City, 
Setubal Province, Portugal, and Islamabad, Pakistan, and at the 
Madagascan metropolitan special police headquarters, the Lagos 
Liaison Office of the General Film Bureau of Nigeria and the sky 
line company of Thailand. 

</TEXT>

