<H3> <TI>   Further on Celebration of Kim Il-song Birthday </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Celebration of Kim Il-song Birthday </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Foreign Media Said To Observe Day </H4>

<F P=102> SK2304110494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1015 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2304110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 23 (KCNA) -- Foreign newspapers 
edited special write-ups and radios broadcast special programmes 
on the occasion of the birthday of the great leader President 
Kim Il-song. 
  The Thai paper SIN CHUNG YUAN PAO said under the title 
"President Kim Il-song's Worship of People": 
  President Kim Il-song's worship of the popular masses 
epitomizes deep respect, care and love for them, devoted service 
for them, absolute belief in their great strength and reliance 
on it. 
  Korea's compulsory free education, free medical care, 
abolition of taxation, free grant of dwelling houses built at 
state expenses, that make people happy, are all a fruition of 
the president's worship of the people. 
  The people express their feelings, saying they owe their 
motherland and future to the leader who backs and leads them. 
  The noble relations of kinship between the leader and the 
people who worship each other produced Korea's unique society 
where the leader and the people are closely united into one. 
  The Thai paper XING SAN RIBAO carried an article headlined 
"President Kim Il-song's Motto -- To Believe in the People as in 
Heaven." 
  The Ugandan paper MUNNO, the Nepalese paper RISING NEPAL and 
the Romanian magazine EUROPA also dedicated articles to April 15. 
  The Russian paper PATRIOT devoted two whole pages to special 
writeups under headline "For Happiness of the People and 
Prosperity of the Country" with a portrait of President Kim 
Il-song. 

</TEXT>

