<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Leaders Greet Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Party Leaders Greet Kim Il-song </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2504111494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1015 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received solidarity messages supporting 
the struggle of the Korean people to defend national dignity and 
sovereignty of the country from general secretary of the popular 
force organized in Costa Rica Jose Francisco Aguilar Bulgarelli, 
chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students 
of Peru Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, general secretary of the 
Central Committee of the Communist Party of Peru (Red 
Motherland) Alberto Moreno, acting leader of the February 18th 
Movement of Trinidad and Tobago Vincent Cabrea, general 
secretary of the Central Committee of the Dominican Communist 
Pary (Marxism-Leninism) Leopoldo Grullon and federal secretary 
of the Communist Party of Austria Walter Bayer. 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song and the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il received a solidarity message from chairman 
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Denmark 
(Marxist-Leninist) Klaus Riis. 
  The solidarity messages say the just stand maintained by the 
government of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea is a 
guideline of the world people's struggle to defend freedom and 
independence against aggression and interference of the 
imperialists and fully support it. 
  Noting that the struggle of the Korean people is one to 
defend national sovereignty and socialism and to reunify the 
country and nation in a peaceful way, the messages state that 
they would extend firm solidarity to the struggle of the Korean 
people in the future, too. 

</TEXT>

