<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song 
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea sent a message of 
greetings on April 24 to President Ali Hassan Mwinyi of the 
United Republic of Tanzania on the occasion of the 30th founding 
anniversary of the republic. 
  President Kim Il-song in his message said the founding of 
the 
United Republic of Tanzania was an event of great importance in 
the history of the Tanzanian people and a great progress has 
been made in Tanzania in the work for national unity and the 
building of a new society in the past 30 years. 
  He wished the president and people of Tanzania big success 
in 
the work for the independent development of the country and 
expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations 
between the two countries would continue to develop on good 
terms. 

