<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Events Marking KPA Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Events Marking KPA Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Choe Kwang Meets Military Attaches </H4>

<F P=102> SK2504092794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2504092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The military attaches of embassies of various 
countries visited the Ministry of People's Armed Forces on 24 
April and enthusiastically congratulated the 62d anniversary of 
the founding of the heroic Korean People's Army [KPA]. 
  Comrade Choe Kwang, chief of the General Staff of the KPA, 
and officers and men and military officers of the KPA welcomed 
the guests. 
  During the meeting, the military attache of the Russian 
Embassy Georgiy Mariyasov, who is the head of the military 
attaches corps, said that he sends warm military greetings to 
all the officers and men of the KPA who are welcoming the 62d 
anniversary of its founding. He also continued: 
  The KPA that has a glorious history of 62 years overcame all 
difficulties and reliably defended the fatherland's security and 
the country's sovereign rights. The KPA founded by the 
respected and beloved leader not only achieved a great victory 
in the anti-Japanese armed struggle, but it was all the more 
developed into a strong regular armed force. 
  Today the KPA is highly upholding Comrade Kim Chong-il, who 
is a great man [widaehan pun], as its supreme commander. We are 
glad over the fact that the Korean people and soldiers of the 
People's Army are able to uphold two great leaders [widaehan 
tubunui yongdoja]. On the anniversary of the KPA, we give our 
sincere greetings to those great leaders. 
  Currently, the imperialists are strengthening pressure and 
maneuvers of isolation toward the DPRK. We actively support all 
the just steps taken by your country against the imperialists' 
unreasonable maneuvers. We hope that there will be greater 
results in the Korean people's struggle to strengthen socialist 
construction and the country's defense capabilities, and to 
reunify the fatherland. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

