<H4>    Receptions Held 23 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> SK2404072594 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2404072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of People's Armed Forces arranged a 
banquet on the evening of 23 April on the 62d anniversary of the 
founding of the heroic Korean People's Army [KPA]. Invited to 
the banquet were the military attaches from the embassies of 
many countries in our country. 
  Present at the banquet were generals and officers, including 
KPA Vice Marshal Kim Kwang-chin, Colonel General Pak Chae-kyong, 
and Lieutenant General An Pi-tok. Speeches were made at the 
banquet. 
  The participants in the banquet toasted to the long life and 
good health of the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song, to the long 
life and good health of the dear leader and KPA Supreme 
Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il, and to the long life and good 
health of the heads of state of the friendly countries 
represented by the military attaches. 
  In addition, the KPA delegation of the Military Armistice 
Commission gave a reception on the evening of 23 April. 

</TEXT>

