<H4>    Senior Officials Lay Wreaths </H4>

<F P=102> SK2504105194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0959 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2504105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Senior party and 
government officials, People's Army [KPA] servicemen and working 
people laid baskets of flowers at the monument to the victorious 
fatherland liberation war today on the 62d anniversary of the 
foundation of the heroic Korean People's Army. 
  Pak Song-chol and Kim Yong-nam were among those senior party 
and government officials. 
  Laid there were floral baskets from the Central Committee of 
the Workers' Party of Korea, the Central People's Committee and 
the Administration Council of the DPRK. 
  Floral baskets were also laid in the name of the Ministry of 
People's Armed Forces, the Ministry of Public Security, 
ministries of the Administration Council, working people's 
organizations, KPA units, and Pyongyang municipal party and 
power organs and administrative and economic bodies. 
  The military attaches corps in Pyongyang laid a floral 
basket 
at the monument today. 

</TEXT>

