<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Events Marking KPA Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Events Marking KPA Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Party, Government Officials Visit Units </H4>

<F P=102> SK2604053094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0513 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2604053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 26 (KCNA) -- Senior party and 
government officials paid calls at units of the Korean People's 
Army [KPA] and the Korean People's Security Forces [KPSF] on 
the 62nd anniversary of the founding of the heroic Korean 
People's Army. 
  Visiting the units of three services of the KPA and the KPSF 
were senior party and government officials including Premier 
Kang Song-san and secretaries of the C.C. [Central Committee], 
the Workers' Party of Korea Kye Ung-tae, Chon Pyong-ho and Han 
Song-yong, who are members of the Political Bureau of the party 
Central Committee, chief officials of the commissions and 
ministries of the Administration Council and central organs and 
chief officials of the local party and government bodies and 
administrative and economic organs. 
  The senior party and government officials conveyed to the 
units gifts sent by the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il, 
chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea and Supreme Commander of the Korean 
People's Army. 
  Touched by the boundless love and care shown by Supreme 
Commander Comrade Kim Chong-il, the soldiers renewed their 
loyal pledge to become guns and bombs defending the party and 
the leader politically and ideologically and with their lives, 
and defend the sky, the land and the sea of the socialist 
motherland as an impregnable fortress. 
  Before seeing the combat and political training of the 
soldiers and their life, the visitors heard about the history of 
the units that had covered a road of victory and glory under the 
tested guidance of Comrade Kim Chong-il, supreme commander of 
the Korean People's Army, holding the great leader President Kim 
Il-song in high esteem. 
  People's delegations attended colourful functions held at 
the 
units of the three services of the KPA and units of the KPSF on 
the Army Day, deepening the feelings between the Army and the 
people. 
  With the delegations present, meetings were held at the 
units 
to convey gifts from Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  On the Army Day, more than 20 art groups comprising 
Pyongyang 
and local artistes gave performances at the units of the three 
services of the KPA to warmly congratulate them. 
  On April 25, an evening of men and officers of the Ministry 
of the People's Armed Forces was held at the Jonsung Square in 
Pyongyang. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

