<H3> <TI>   Further on Events Marking KPA Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Events Marking KPA Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Art Studio Showcases Paintings </H4>

<F P=102> SK2604103694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1013 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2604103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 26 (KCNA) -- The Mansudae Art 
Studio has created a number of works of art of various themes to 
greet the Korean People's Army Day (April 25). 
  Included in the works are Korean and oil paintings 
portraying 
on canvases of high ideological and artistic standard Comrade 
Kim Chong-il, supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, who 
is possessed of the chuche-based military idea, extraordinary 
intelligence, matchless grit and warm love. 
  "Supreme Commander General Kim Chong-il Guiding an 
Operational Meeting", "Opening the Route of the Era", "Merciless 
Punishment on Provokers" and other Korean paintings portray 
Comrade Kim Chong-il who is rearing the KPA into an invincible, 
matchless army with the chuche-based military idea and unique 
tactics at the head of the revolutionary armed forces. 
  "Respected Supreme Commander Marshal Kim Chong-il Guiding 
Combined Tactical Drill", a Korean painting portraying him 
guiding a coordinated operational drill of mechanized units of 
the three services on a mountain side with binoculars in his 
hand also successfully represents the looks of the great 
brilliant commander. 
  The Korean paintings "Father of Soldiers" and "The Dear 
Leader Calling at a Post", the oil painting "Supreme Commander 
General Kim Chong-il Among Soldiers" and many other works show 
the noble virtues of Comrade Kim Chong-il who always visits 
soldiers and bestows tender loving care on them. 

</TEXT>

