<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Delegation From PRC Visits Hanoi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic Delegation From PRC Visits Hanoi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2804094194 Hanoi VNA in English 0605 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2804094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 28 -- An economic and commercial 
delegation of Liaoning Province of China led by Mr. Gao Guozhou, 
deputy governor of the province, paid a working visit to Vietnam 
at the invitation of the Vietnam Chamber of Commerce and 
Industry (VCCI). 
  The delegation includes many Chinese managers and 
businessmen 
in the fields of economy, trade, energy, finance and chemicals. 
  While here, the delegation had working sessions with Mr. 
Doan 
Ngoc Bong, VCCI's first vice president. The two sides informed 
each other of the situations in and possibilities for economic 
and commercial cooperation between Vietnam and Liaoning. The 
guests expressed their wish to cooperate with Vietnam in the 
fields of investment, trade, infrastructural construction, and 
especially to participate in improvement of factories formerly 
built with Chinese assistance. 
  The delegation also had working sessions with leaders of the 
Ministries of Trade, Energy, Construction, and Heavy Industry, 
and called at several economic and commercial establishments to 
enquire into possibilities and opportunities for investment, 
joint-ventures and commercial cooperation between the two sides. 

</TEXT>

