<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Justice Minister Shigeto Nagano </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804121194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0948 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- New Justice Minister 
Shigeto Nagano of Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party] is a former 
chief of staff of the Ground Self-Defense Force (GSDF). He 
replaced Akira Mikazuki, a distinguished academic, as justice 
minister. 
  Nagano, 71, graduated from the former elite Japanese 
Military 
Academy and assumed the post of first lieutenant in the Japanese 
Imperial Army in 1945 when World War II ended. 
  He entered the police reserve force in 1951, which was 
upgraded to the Self-Defense Forces (SDF) in 1954. Before 
retiring from the GSDF in 1980, he was promoted to the top 
uniform rank. 
  Nagano won his first seat in the House of Councillors in the 
1986 election for which he had run as a candidate of the then 
ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP). He is now serving as an 
upper house member for the second six-year term. 
  In June 1993, he joined other LDP defectors to set up 
Shinseito (Japan Renewal Party), which two months later formed 
the coalition government with six other non-LDP parties. 
  Nagano comes from Oita Prefecture on Kyushu Island in 
western 
Japan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-7194 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas082_a_94019" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-082 </AU>
