<H3> <TI>   Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Telecommunications Minister Hikasa </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804080994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0724 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- New Posts and 
Telecommunications Minister Katsuyuki Hikasa is one of the main 
policy experts in Buddhist-backed Komeito [Clean Government 
Party], an influential party in the coalition government. 
  Hikasa, 48, Komeito's Policy Board chairman, has never 
failed 
to peruse the bulk of budget documents every year ever since the 
party was in the opposition camp until last August. He played 
an active role in the ruling parties to draft 1994 budget bills 
and a tax reform plan. 
  Hikasa replaced Takenori Kanzaki, his comrade in Komeito. 
Hikasa is said to be friendly and is well versed in ancient 
arts and ceramics. 
  He has been elected a House of Representatives legislator 
four times from the No. 1 constituency in Okayama Prefecture. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

