<H3> <TI>   Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Transport Minister Nobuaki Futami </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804080094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0716 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- Newly named Transport 
Minister Nobuaki Futami is a distinguished debater and member of 
the Buddhist-backed Komeito [Clean Government Party], succeeding 
Shigeru Ito of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) [of Japan -- 
SDPJ]. He rose swiftly through the ranks of Komeito, serving as 
political editor and an editor-in-chief of the party's newspaper 
KOMEI SHIMBUN before being elected to the House of 
Representatives from a constituency in Ibaraki Prefecture. 
  The 59-year-old legislator is well-versed in a wide range of 
policy affairs. He chaired the party's Policy Affairs Council 
for three years. 
  Futami has also been active in addressing environmental 
issues, particularly water pollution. 
  He is popular among legislators, including members of the 
main opposition Liberal Democratic Party. He has a reputation 
for being lighthearted and sensitive. 
  Born in Tokyo, Futami completed graduate school at the 
prestigious Waseda University. He is currently serving as vice 
chairman of Komeito. 
  He has been elected to the powerful lower house for seven 
times. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

