<H3> <TI>   Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Biographical Sketches of New Cabinet Members </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sci-Tech Agency Leader Mikio Omi </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804080594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0718 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804080594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 28 KYODO -- Newly appointed Science 
and Technology Agency Chief Mikio Omi is known to have 
interpellated 488 times at the Diet, the largest number among 
all lawmakers. The record number of interpellators came from 
his belief that legislators should be spokespersons for the 
people. 
  Omi, 58, is a House of Representatives legislator of Komeito 
[Clean Government Party] backed by the Buddhist group Soka 
Gakkai, an influential party in the coalition government. He 
succeeded Satsuki Eda of the United Social Democratic Party 
(USDP). 
  Some party members said he is earnest and warmhearted. 
  Born and brought up in Osaka, Omi has been elected from the 
No.3 constituency in Osaka Prefecture nine times since 1967, but 
he has not held any conspicuous post in the party. 
  In 1967, the third Komeito Chairman Yoshikatsu Takeiri, the 
forth Chairman Junya Yano and the fifth and current Chairman 
Koshiro Ishida were also elected lower house members for the 
first time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

